#### Java and JMeter Project created for learning purposes

## Project description
    This project is a simple RESTful web service built using Spring Boot, exposing a
    /greetings endpoint that supports both POST and GET operations. It also includes a
    JMeter test plan to simulate HTTP load and validate the API performance.
    - pom.xml is a configuartion file used by Maven.
    - GreetingsApplication contains tests.
    - MyObject creates JSON format.
    - test-plan.jmx is a test plan for performance testing in JMeter. This file contains information which
      endpoints to test (eg. POST to /greetings), how many users etc.
    - Directory /jmeter-test/photos contains screens of JMeter tool.


# Running command below, starts a web server on port 8081 and it is possible to send POST/GET requests
# eg. via JMeter or curl
    mvn spring-boot:run

# Link to access GET request with greetings to Katarzyna
    http://localhost:8081/greetings

# POST curl command on Unix system:
    curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/greetings -H "Content-Type: text/plain" -d "Katarzyna"
    
# POST command on Windows system:
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "http://localhost:8081/greetings"
  -Method Post `
  -Body "Katarzyna" `
  -ContentType "text/plain"


